IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: HELP YOUNG PEOPLE TRANSFORM THEIR LIVES BY DEVELOPING THE CONFIDENCE AND SKILLS TO LIVE, LEARN & EARN.
IRS990.MissionDesc: PRINCE'S TRUST USA AIMS TO SUPPORT THE GLOBAL WORK OF THE PRINCE'S TRUST. TOGETHER WITH OUR PARTNERS, OUR MISSION IS TO HELP YOUNG PEOPLE TRANSFORM THEIR LIVES BY DEVELOPING THE CONFIDENCE AND SKILLS TO LIVE, LEARN AND EARN.
IRS990.Desc: THERE ARE THREE SIGNIFICANT GLOBAL CHALLENGES THAT DRIVE THE WORK OF THE TRUST: THE RISING LEVELS OF YOUTH UNEMPLOYMENT (OVER 70 MILLION); THE LOW LEVELS OF SECONDARY EDUCATION COMPLETION (264 MILLION CHILDREN AND YOUNG PEOPLE OUT OF SCHOOL) AND THE WORLD'S RAPIDLY CHANGING POPULATIONS (OVER HALF OF THE GLOBAL POPULATION IS NOW UNDER 30).IN LIGHT OF THAT, THE MAIN PRIORITY IS TO HELP YOUNG PEOPLE TO IMPROVE THEIR LIVES THROUGH PARTNERSHIPS DELIVERING PRACTICAL SOLUTIONS THAT LEAD TO IMPROVED CONFIDENCE. THESE HELP SKILL YOUNG PEOPLE FOR WORK, SUPPORT THEM IN EDUCATION OR HELP THEM SET UP BUSINESSES.DURING FY23 THE ORGANIZATION RAISED FUNDS THAT WERE GRANTED TO ITS PARENT ORGANIZATION, PRINCE'S TRUST, A UK BASED ORGANIZATION.

AccountActivitiesOutsideUSGrp.SpecificServicesProvidedTxt: STAFF SUPPORT FOR US LAUNCH OF YOUTH-SERVING PROGRAMS

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ESTABLISHED IN 2019 TO BENEFIT GLOBAL YOUTH, INCLUDING WITHIN THE USA. WE ALSO SUPPORT ESTABLISHED PROGRAMMING ABROAD (VIA OUR PARENT CHARITY, THE PRINCE'S TRUST) WHICH HAS SERVED OVER A MILLION YOUNG PEOPLE WORLDWIDE, OVER THE LAST 45 YEARS. AS A RESULT OF OUR YOUTH PROGRAMMING IN 20 COUNTRIES WORLDWIDE, THE PRINCE'S TRUST USA ENSURES THAT: - THREE IN FOUR YOUNG PEOPLE SUPPORTED BY THE PRINCE'S TRUST MOVE INTO WORK, TRAINING, OR EDUCATION. - A GOAL OF APPROXIMATELY $0.87 OF EVERY $1 DONATED TO THE PRINCE'S TRUST IS SPENT ON YOUTH PROGRAMMING. EACH DONATION IS SUBJECT TO STAFF AND BOARD REVIEWS AND APPROVALS BEFORE BEING GRANTED. WE ALSO ENGAGE TRUSTED PARTNER ORGANIZATIONS TO DELIVER SERVICES TO YOUTH. INDIVIDUAL RECIPROCATE CHARITY ARE RESPONSIBLE TO PROVIDE UPDATES ON DELIVERABLES AND MEASURABLE OUTCOMES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 4
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DURING FY23, THE ORGANIZATION AMENDED ITS BY-LAWS AS FOLLOWS: - THE NUMBER OF TRUSTEES OF THE BOARD SHOULD NOT BE LESS THAN 3 OR GREATER THAN 20. - EACH TRUSTEE SHALL BE ELECTED FOR A TERM OF THREE YEARS AND SHOULD NOT EXCEED FIVE YEARS. NO TRUSTEE SHALL SERVE ON THE BOARD FOR MORE THAN TWO CONSECUTIVE THREE YEAR TERMS. - THE ORGANIZATION'S SOLE MEMBER PRINCE'S TRUST RESIGNED AS SOLE MEMBER AND PRINCE'S TRUST GROUP COMPANY WAS APPOINTED AS THE NEW SOLE MEMBER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE SOLE MEMBER HAS THE POWER TO REMOVE BOARD MEMBERS, APPROVE ANY DISSOLUTION OR TO AMEND ANY GOVERNING DOCUMENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD ACTS ON BEHALF OF THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PRINCE'S TRUST AMERICA, INC. HAS ITS FORM 990 PREPARED BY AN OUTSIDE ACCOUNTING FIRM AND HAS ESTABLISHED THE FOLLOWING REVIEW PROCESS TO ENSURE THAT THE INFORMATION REPORTED IS COMPLETE AND ACCURATE. WHEN THE FORM 990 HAS BEEN PREPARED AND IT'S READY TO BE FILED WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE IT IS REVIEWED BY THE CEO AND THEN ELECTRONICALLY SENT TO THE BOARD FOR APPROVAL. UPON BOARD APPROVAL THE RETURN IS FILED WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY APPLIES TO DIRECTORS, OFFICERS OR KEY PERSONS OF THE ORGANIZATION. ANNUALLY, ALL APPLICABLE PERSONS ARE REQUIRED TO COMPLETE AN ANNUAL DISCLOSURE STATEMENT. THESE INDIVIDUALS HAVE A DUTY TO DISCLOSE ANY ACTUAL OR POSSIBLE CONFLICT OF INTEREST AND GIVE ALL MATERIAL FACTS TO THE BOARD. AFTER DISCLOSURE THE INTERESTED PERSON SHALL LEAVE THE BOARD MEETING WHILE THE DETERMINATION OF A CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS DISCUSSED AND VOTED UPON BY THE REMAINING BOARD MEMBERS. THE REMAINING BOARD MEMBERS DECISION WILL BE DOCUMENTED IN THE BOARD MINUTES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMPENSATION OF THE CEO AND KEY EMPLOYEE ARE REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE ORGANIZATION ENGAGES AN INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT TO CONDUCT AN INDEPENDENT SALARY REVIEW AND USES VARIOUS COMPENSATION DATA FOR CEOS AND OTHER PERSONS OF FUNCTIONALLY COMPARABLE POSITIONS FOR SIMILARLY QUALIFIED PERSONS AT SIMILARLY SITUATED ORGANIZATIONS. THE ORGANIZATION MAINTAINS CONTEMPORANEOUS DOCUMENTATION OF ITS PROCEEDINGS, DELIBERATIONS AND SUPPORTING DECISIONS IN ITS BOARD MINUTES. THE PROCESS WAS LAST UNDERTAKEN DURING THE YEAR 2023.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS FORM 990 AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION AS REQUIRED UNDER SECTION 6104 OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THE RETURN IS ALSO POSTED ON GUIDESTAR.ORG AND OTHER SIMILAR TYPES OF WEBSITES. IN ADDITION, THE FORM 1023, FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION AND BY-LAWS ARE ALSO AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST.
